{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"12-hole doughnut trays, bowl, wire rack, piping bag with a plain nozzle (1 cm), oven","id":"r391312","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-xG9C9_98158\/XZWdtpTvO8I\/AAAAAAAAepY\/by76yxjd39g78UY_fsgxpwQ1ENv8sok_QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LXlkzhGguYDJyNEX.png","title":"Spiced chocolate doughnuts","publishedAt":"2019-05-06T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"150 g butter, cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"1 tbsp raw sugar"},{"content":"2 tsp ground cinnamon"},{"content":"200 g almonds (activated or roasted)"},{"content":"200 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa), broken into pieces"},{"content":"150 g Rapadura sugar (see Tips)"},{"content":"½ tsp gluten free baking powder"},{"content":"5 eggs"},{"content":"1 tsp natural vanilla extract"},{"content":"½ tsp ground cardamom"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"14.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"10.8 g","calories":"784.3 kJ \/ 186.7 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 160°C. Grease 2 x 12-hole doughnut trays and set aside."},{"content":"Place raw sugar and 1 teaspoon of the cinnamon into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place almonds into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b> or until finely ground. Transfer into a separate bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter and melt <b>2 min 30 sec\/80°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add Rapadura sugar, baking powder, eggs, vanilla, cardamom, remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon and reserved milled almonds and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Transfer mixture into a piping bag with a plain nozzle (1 cm). Pipe mixture into prepared doughnut trays, then bake for 15 minutes (160°C) or until just cooked. Allow to cool in tray for 15 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely. Dust doughnuts with reserved cinnamon sugar before serving (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Baby's serve<\/strong>: because these doughnuts include some added sugar, you should ideally wait until your child is over 12 months before serving.","<strong>Toddler's serve<\/strong>: serve as is as an occasional treat, cut up as needed, keeping serving sizes small.","You can replace the Rapadura sugar with coconut sugar in this recipe.","You can serve the doughnuts without the cinnamon sugar, simply omit milling the sugar and reduce the cinnamon to 1 teaspoon."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","45m","24 portions"]}